Tailwind now just applies two properties to the same class for instance when u add `delay-300` it adds the two css classes below
```
.delay-300 {
    transition-delay: 300ms;
}
.delay-300 {
    animation-delay: 300ms;
}
```
and same for `duration-300`
```
.duration-300 {
    transition-duration: 300ms;
}
.duration-300 {
    animation-duration: 300ms;
}
```
This fixes the problem for animation. But this is missing from the docs. Hopefully this gets added to the docs

